    <item>
      <title>Life, Death, and the Illusion of Reasons</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/life-death-and-illusion-of-reasons/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>hari@dasarpai.com (Dr. Hari Thapliyaal)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/wiaposts/life-death-and-illusion-of-reasons/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;
    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;../../assets/images/wiapost/5294-life-death-and-illusion-of-reasons.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Life, Death, and the Illusion of Reasons&#34; /&gt;
      
    &lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Life, Death, and the Illusion of Reasons&lt;/strong&gt; 
    &lt;div id=&#34;life-death-and-the-illusion-of-reasons&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
    &lt;span
        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;
        &lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34;
            style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#life-death-and-the-illusion-of-reasons&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Out of habit, we ask when someone dies,&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Oh, how did he die?&amp;rdquo;&lt;br&gt;
He was young,&lt;br&gt;
He was good, religious,&lt;br&gt;
He practiced yoga, cared for his health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Out of habit, we ask when someone suffers,&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;Oh, why is he suffering?&amp;rdquo;&lt;br&gt;
He is a good person,&lt;br&gt;
A virtuous soul.&lt;br&gt;
Sometimes we say,&lt;br&gt;
&amp;ldquo;He has already suffered enough,&lt;br&gt;
Why must he endure more?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
